## Azure  steps by VM Creation
Login to Azure portal console
search the VM- Select and create a VM


Project details : Subscription --> Azure Subscription
Resources group : Development
Instance details
VM Name : Develop
Region: Central India
Availability zone : AZ
Zone options : Self selected zone
Availability zone : Zone 2, Zone 3
Security groups : Trusted launch VM
Image : select OS type : select windows (Ubuntu, Windows, Linux, Redhat)
vm architecture : X64
Size : Default
Administrator account
Authentication type : SSH public key
username : azureuser
SSH public key source : generate a new key pair
SSH key type : RSA SSH format
keypair name : develop
inbound port rules
     Public inbound ports : allow selected ports
     select inbound ports : SSH 22, http , http, rdp

Disk details : default
Networking :default
Management : default 
Monitoring : default
advanced: default
tags : default
review and create 
click create
VM created successfully.
click connect --> Connect download RDP file.

install RDP
Search : RDP 
Host name /ip : 40.81.213.217
username :ravi
upload : pem file
password: windows@12345

Result : windows server open : browser page

inside the Windows server page: search the SERVER MANAGER --> add roles & features v--> next 
role based or feature based installation
select a server from server pool --> win -- > next -- select IIS --> Add features --> Next (3) --> install

Result  :  Open the browser : IIS Server page open



